<http://dx.doi.org/10.1093/zoolinnean/zlaa128>
    bibo:endPage "216" ;
    bibo:issue "1" ;
    bibo:journal "Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2021-09-01" ;
    bibo:startPage "199" ;
    bibo:volume "193" ;
    dc:creator "Ferrari, Rafael R; Packer, Laurence" ;
    dc:date "2021" ;
    dc:title "Morphological phylogeny and review of the generic classification of Colletinae (Hymenoptera: Colletidae)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10133154>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10133166>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10133162> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10133154>
    dc:description "Figure 1. Lateral habitus of some Colletinae showing some of their diversity. A–P, females, Hemicotelles magallanes (A), H. ruizii (B), Mourecotelles mixtus (C), Mourecotelles sp.1 (D), Xanthocotelles atacama (E), X. fritzi (F), Colletes cyanescens (G), C. cyaniventris (H), C. fulvipes (I), C. halophilus (J), C. nigritulus (K), C. petropolitanus (L), C. rugicollis (M), C. slevini (N), C. solidaginis (O) and C. zuluensis (P). Scale bars = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10133154/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10133166>
    dc:description "Figure 6. Most-parsimonious tree (part two) from the EW analysis showing character state changes. Black rectangles represent unique changes and white rectangles represent homoplastic ones. Character numbers are indicated above branches and the corresponding state changes below the branches. Asterisks indicate type species of the genus. The position of Colletes clypeonitens is doubtful (see text). The Colletinae shown are (from top to bottom) Hemicotelles ruizii, C. cyanescens, C. nigritulus and C. slevini." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10133166/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10133162>
    dc:description "Figure 4. Diagnostic features of Colletinae. Numbers shown in red indicate derived character states. A, B, Lateral view of male propodeum, Trichocolletes dowerinensis (A) and Colletes gilvus (B); C–E, posterior view of male metapostnotum, Xanthocotelles atacama (C), Hemicotelles magallanes (D) and C. atripes (E); F, ventral view of male S7 of Mourecotelles sp.1. Scale bars = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10133162/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

